{
  "texts": [
    "In a somewhat peculiar exploration in 2014, van Hague et al. [31] identified the frequency of numbers found in the 2012 version of CC, showing that the (overwhelmingly positive) numbers found across web pages do follow the Power law distribution.These works gave us insight into how researchers approach the problem of analysing and quantifying phenomena in large text corpora.",
    "We propose our own method of quantifying geospatial in CC in the following section.",
    "Our aim is to estimate what share of documents in a typical CC release contains any geospatial information as defined in Subsection 3.2.",
    "We deliberately avoid labelling and then quantifying the actual geospatial text as our delineation criteria and judgement of relevance would get extremely complex.",
    "About Common CrawlCommon Crawl is a San-Francisco based non-profit organisation."
  ]
}